# Week 1, Homework

The homework problems in this set fall into four groups:

- [Memorizing truth-tables](#memorizing-truth-tables)

- [More memorizing truth-tables](#more-memorizing-truth-tables)

- [Finding the main connectives](#finding-the-main-connectives)

- [More complex truth-tables](#more-complex-truth-tables)

There are 20 problems total, each equally weighted. Submitted problems received on time receive 5 points each, and late submissions receive 2 points each. Hence, there are 80 possible points.

You can check your answer with the "Check" button next to each problem. After you have checked your answer, **you must press the "Submit" button** next to the problem. If you do not do this, you will **not** get credit for the problem. Once you have submitted your answer, your points are recorded. You can always check your points by going to the "user home" at the top right. You must be signed in in order to submit your answers.

If you want to do some problems at one point in time and other problems at another point in time, you can do that by just coming back to this assignment page. Once submitted, your points are permanently recorded. If you return to this page later or refresh this page, it won't display your previously recorded answers, but again your points are permanently recorded. If you have forgotten which ones you still need to do, you can check your points by going to the "user home" at the top right.

