## Memorizing truth-tables

The following homework problems are intended to help you memorize the truth-tables for the propositional connectives. Only one of the rows are given, and this is designed to help you memorize the truth-tables row-by-row, and to make sure that your recall of this is not tied to the particular order we happened to enumerate the rows in.

These problems only presuppose [Week 1, Lecture 1](https://carnap.io/shared/logicteaching@g.ucla.edu/week01-lecture1-connectives.pandoc).

~~~{.TruthTable .Partial system="gamutPND" options="nodash nocounterexample autoAtoms"}
1.01 p/\q
| F - F
~~~

~~~{.TruthTable .Partial system="gamutPND" options="nodash nocounterexample autoAtoms"}
1.02 p\/q
| F - F
~~~

~~~{.TruthTable .Partial system="gamutPND" options="nodash nocounterexample autoAtoms"}
1.03 p->q
| F - F
~~~

~~~{.TruthTable .Partial system="gamutPND" options="nodash nocounterexample autoAtoms"}
1.04 p/\q
